FAQS['15-cheapest-countries-to-visit-from-indonesia-in-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"What is the single cheapest country to visit from Indonesia?","a":"For most Indonesians, Malaysia wins on total cost because flights from Jakarta are extremely cheap and daily spending is low. For the lowest on-the-ground costs once you arrive, Vietnam, Cambodia, Laos and India are hard to beat. Your final answer depends on flight deals and dates — and always confirm the visa for your route on the Visa Wizard."},{"q":"Can Indonesians travel visa-free around ASEAN?","a":"Indonesia holds a strong ASEAN passport and short tourist visits between member states are generally straightforward, which is why nearby countries dominate this list. But conditions, permitted stays and entry rules differ by route and change often. Never assume — confirm your specific passport-and-destination combination on the VisitPlane Visa Wizard before booking anything non-refundable."},{"q":"Do Indonesians need a visa for Thailand or Malaysia?","a":"For short tourism, Indonesians typically find both Thailand and Malaysia among the easiest neighbours to visit, which is exactly why they top this guide. However, rules, stay limits and conditions can change at any time. We never quote a fixed outcome here — run your exact route through the Visa Wizard and check the Indonesia to Malaysia page for the current requirement."},{"q":"When is the cheapest time to travel for Indonesians?","a":"Aim for shoulder seasons and steer clear of Indonesia's big peaks — Lebaran, the December–January holidays and school breaks — when flights and rooms spike. Booking mid-week, setting fare alerts on budget carriers from Jakarta and Bali, and staying flexible with dates all push prices down. The cheapest months vary by destination, so compare a few."},{"q":"How can I keep daily costs low on these trips?","a":"Eat where locals eat, sleep in guesthouses or dorms, and use public buses, trains and ferries instead of taxis. Mainland Southeast Asia and South Asia reward this approach hugely, with street food and local transport costing very little. Withdraw local currency from ATMs rather than airport counters, and carry some US dollars as a backup in places like Cambodia."},{"q":"Which destinations are best reached overland from Indonesia?","a":"Timor-Leste is the standout, reachable overland from West Timor, and once you are in mainland ASEAN you can move cheaply by bus and train between Thailand, Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam. Brunei pairs naturally with a Borneo trip from Sabah or Sarawak. Most other picks need a flight. Always confirm border-crossing and visa details on the Visa Wizard first."},{"q":"Are Singapore and Hong Kong too expensive for budget travellers?","a":"Not if you keep stays short. Both have pricey hotels but loads of free sights — skylines, parks, light shows — and superb, cheap local food at hawker centres and noodle shops. Treat them as polished two-or-three-day add-ons rather than long stays, lean on public transport, and they fit a budget trip comfortably. Confirm your entry route on the Wizard."},{"q":"Is the Maldives realistic on a budget from Indonesia?","a":"Yes, increasingly so. By staying on local inhabited islands instead of private resorts, you get the same turquoise water and snorkelling for a fraction of the cost, eating at local cafés and using public ferries between atolls. It is the priciest of our cheap picks but offers astonishing value. Flights route via a hub, and you should confirm the visa on the Visa Wizard."}]''')

FAQS['15-cheapest-countries-to-visit-from-vietnam-in-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"What is the cheapest country to visit from Vietnam in 2026?","a":"Cambodia is usually the cheapest, mainly because you can reach it overland by sleeper bus from Ho Chi Minh City, skipping airfare entirely. Once there, guesthouses, street food and tuk-tuks cost very little. Laos and Myanmar are similarly low-cost. Always check your personal entry requirement on the VisitPlane Visa Wizard before booking."},{"q":"Can I travel overland from Vietnam to Cambodia and Laos?","a":"Yes — Vietnam shares land borders with both, and sleeper buses regularly cross from Ho Chi Minh City to Phnom Penh and from northern and central Vietnam into Laos. Overland travel is far cheaper than flying and avoids airport fees. Entry rules still apply at land borders, so confirm your requirement on the Visa Wizard before you travel."},{"q":"Are these 15 countries visa-free for Vietnamese passport holders?","a":"Not necessarily. This is a cost-and-value guide, not a visa-free list. Entry rules — visa, visa-on-arrival, e-visa or otherwise — vary by country and change often, and they depend on your specific passport and trip. Run each destination through the VisitPlane Visa Wizard to see exactly what applies to you before booking."},{"q":"How can I find the cheapest flights from Hanoi or Ho Chi Minh City?","a":"Budget carriers like VietJet, AirAsia and Vietnam Airlines run frequent promotions from both cities. Set fare alerts, travel midweek, fly with cabin baggage only, and avoid Tet and major Vietnamese holiday peaks when prices spike. For nearby Cambodia and Laos, overland buses often beat any flight on price."},{"q":"Is Singapore too expensive for a budget trip from Vietnam?","a":"Singapore has higher accommodation costs, but it can still be done cheaply. Many of its best experiences — Gardens by the Bay's outdoor areas, Marina Bay, parks and museums — are free or low-cost, and hawker centres serve excellent meals for a few dollars. Treat it as a short stop within a wider regional trip to keep spending down."},{"q":"Is Kyrgyzstan realistic for Vietnamese travellers?","a":"Yes, and it is one of the most interesting emerging-bargain options. Reached via connecting flights into Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan offers mountains, alpine lakes and yurt stays at low daily costs. Central Asia is opening up for budget travel. Because the rules are less familiar, give yourself extra time to check your entry requirement on the VisitPlane Visa Wizard."},{"q":"When is the cheapest time to travel from Vietnam?","a":"Shoulder seasons generally offer the best mix of low prices and decent weather, with cheaper rooms and thinner crowds than peak periods. Avoid travelling during Tet and major Vietnamese holidays, when both flights and accommodation surge. Booking flights well in advance and staying flexible on dates also helps you catch budget-carrier promotions."},{"q":"How do I avoid booking a trip I can't enter?","a":"Plan in the right order. Shortlist destinations by budget first, then run each through the VisitPlane Visa Wizard to confirm the entry requirement for your Vietnamese passport, then check the document checklist. Only after that should you book non-refundable flights or hotels. This sequence prevents costly mistakes and stops you overpaying for visa services you don't need."}]''')

FAQS['15-cheapest-countries-to-visit-from-kenya-in-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"What is the single cheapest country to visit from Kenya?","a":"For most Nairobi-based travellers it is one of the East African Community neighbours — Tanzania or Uganda — because you can travel overland by bus and daily costs for food, transport and lodging stay shilling-friendly. The biggest expense is often the journey itself, which the bus keeps low. Confirm your entry route with the Visa Wizard before you go."},{"q":"Is overland travel within the East African Community easier for Kenyans?","a":"Generally it is more straightforward to move between East African Community member states, and through-buses run from Nairobi to cities like Kampala, Kigali and Arusha. However, free movement is not the same as a guaranteed entry, and requirements can change. Always confirm the current rules for your specific passport with the Visa Wizard before you travel or book."},{"q":"When is the cheapest time to travel from Nairobi?","a":"Shoulder season — the quieter weeks just before or after peak periods — typically offers the lowest flights and lodging across this list. Travelling mid-week and avoiding major holidays helps too. For regional trips, prices are fairly steady year-round, but for long-haul and island destinations, timing your dates flexibly can make a real difference to the total cost."},{"q":"Can I do a safari on a tight budget?","a":"Yes. Self-drive trips, camping, and parks in Zambia, Zimbabwe and Botswana often cost far less than marquee lodges elsewhere, and East Africa's own parks are reachable overland. Park fees are the main fixed cost, so budget those separately. Travelling in shoulder season and sleeping in budget camps or guesthouses keeps daily spending low while still delivering excellent wildlife."},{"q":"Are Gulf stopovers in the UAE worth it for budget travellers?","a":"They can be. Frequent flights make the UAE an easy add-on to a longer journey, and a short stopover lets you see Dubai or Abu Dhabi without committing to an expensive full stay. Lean on free beaches, public transport and self-catering to keep costs in check. Check your entry requirements with the Visa Wizard before counting on a stopover visit."},{"q":"Which destinations are best reached overland versus by flight?","a":"Tanzania, Uganda and Rwanda are the classic overland trips from Nairobi, with buses making them very affordable. Ethiopia and the Southern Africa picks are better by flight, while the Asian and Gulf destinations require long-haul travel. Choosing the road for nearby countries and saving flights for distant ones is the core of stretching your shilling on this list."},{"q":"Do I need travel insurance for these trips?","a":"It is not always mandatory, but for budget travel it is wise — a single clinic visit or cancelled flight can wipe out the savings a careful trip earned. A flexible travel-medical plan lets you cover only your exact travel dates, keeping the cost small. Check whether any destination on your itinerary requires proof of cover before you depart."},{"q":"How do I confirm the visa situation before booking?","a":"Use the VisitPlane Visa Wizard at /wizard, which gives entry guidance for your specific passport and destination, and review the document checklist for what you may need to prepare. Because rules differ by nationality and change frequently, always confirm the current requirement before booking any non-refundable flights or accommodation, rather than relying on older advice."}]''')

FAQS['15-cheapest-countries-to-visit-from-ghana-in-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"What is the single cheapest country to visit from Ghana?","a":"Togo is usually the cheapest, mainly because you can reach Lomé overland from Accra in a few hours by STC coach or shared taxi, skipping airfare entirely. Local food and guesthouses are very affordable. Benin and Burkina Faso are similarly low-cost once you arrive, though distances and transport add up the further you go."},{"q":"Does ECOWAS free movement mean I can enter without a visa?","a":"ECOWAS arrangements generally make travel between member states easier for nationals of the bloc, which is why nearby West African trips are so accessible from Ghana. However, exact entry conditions, documents, and stay limits differ by situation and can change. Always confirm the current rule for your passport using the VisitPlane Visa Wizard before you travel or book."},{"q":"Can I travel overland from Accra to Togo and Benin?","a":"Yes, the coastal corridor from Accra through Lomé to Cotonou is one of West Africa's most travelled routes. STC and private intercity coaches, plus shared taxis, connect the cities, and many travellers do Togo and Benin as a single road trip. Carry CFA francs and confirm entry requirements for each border before setting off."},{"q":"When is the cheapest time of year to travel from Ghana?","a":"Shoulder seasons — outside major festivals, school holidays, and peak periods — usually offer the lowest airfares and accommodation rates. For regional overland trips, the drier months make road travel more comfortable. Booking flights well in advance and staying flexible with dates helps too. Always weigh weather against price for your specific destination before committing."},{"q":"How far does the cedi go across West Africa?","a":"The cedi stretches well across the region, particularly once you eat locally and use shared transport rather than tourist services. In francophone neighbours like Togo, Benin, and Côte d'Ivoire, the local currency is the CFA franc, so plan to exchange or carry CFA cash. Daily costs in these countries feel very low to moderate for budget-minded Ghanaian travellers."},{"q":"Why should I carry CFA francs?","a":"Togo, Benin, Côte d'Ivoire, Senegal, and Burkina Faso all use the CFA franc, and card acceptance can be limited outside major hotels. Carrying CFA cash means smoother payments for shared taxis, market meals, and small guesthouses, and helps you avoid poor on-the-spot exchange rates. Change money at reputable outlets and keep small denominations handy for everyday spending."},{"q":"Is the UAE a realistic budget trip from Ghana?","a":"It can be. The UAE is a popular shopping and stopover destination, and while flights and hotels are the main costs, on-the-ground spending can stay modest. Free public beaches, the affordable metro, and free attractions in Dubai and Abu Dhabi balance the pricier experiences. Confirm your entry requirement with the VisitPlane Visa Wizard before booking anything non-refundable."},{"q":"Are there any safety considerations for these destinations?","a":"Most destinations on this list are well suited to budget travel, but conditions vary and can change. Parts of Burkina Faso, in particular, have seen security volatility, so check your government's latest travel advice before planning a route there. For every trip, review current advisories, keep travel-medical cover, and stay flexible if conditions shift near your dates."}]''')

FAQS['visa-free-countries-for-indonesia-passport-holders-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"How many countries can Indonesian passport holders visit visa-free?","a":"The commonly cited figure is around 70+ destinations offering visa-free, visa-on-arrival, or easy e-Visa access — but treat that as an approximate sense of scale, not a guarantee. The real number shifts as governments change agreements. For any specific destination, confirm the current rule with the Visa Wizard before booking."},{"q":"Is ASEAN visa-free for Indonesian travellers?","a":"Travel within ASEAN is generally easier for Indonesian passport holders, and short tourist visits to fellow member states are commonly straightforward. However, entry conditions and permitted stay lengths still differ by country, and rules can change. Always confirm the current requirement for your specific route with the Visa Wizard before you travel."},{"q":"What is the difference between visa-free, visa-on-arrival, and e-Visa?","a":"Visa-free means no visa step at all for a tourist stay. Visa-on-arrival means you obtain and usually pay for a visa at the border when you land. An e-Visa or e-TA means you apply online and get approval before flying. Each is a different pre-trip requirement, so check which applies to your route."},{"q":"Why does the visa-free country count keep changing?","a":"Governments add and withdraw bilateral agreements, suspend or reprice visa-on-arrival schemes, and launch new electronic authorisation systems that change a route's category. Health, security, and political events can also shift rules at short notice. That is why any fixed number is only a snapshot — always verify the current rule before you book."},{"q":"Do Indonesians need a visa for Singapore or Thailand?","a":"For Indonesian passport holders, short tourist visits to Singapore and Thailand are typically easy, and these are core ASEAN destinations. That said, exact conditions, stay limits, and entry requirements can change. Rather than rely on a general statement, confirm the current rule for your route with the Visa Wizard before you travel."},{"q":"Which regions are strongest for an Indonesian passport?","a":"The strongest region by far is ASEAN, where short tourist visits are generally easy. Beyond that, Indonesian travellers commonly find convenient access to parts of East Asia such as Hong Kong and Macau, selected Middle East and Eurasia destinations, several African and island nations via visa-on-arrival, and some Americas and Caribbean destinations. Confirm each route individually."},{"q":"How do I check whether I need a visa for a specific country?","a":"Start with the Visa Wizard: enter your Indonesian passport and your destination to get the current category in seconds. Then read the per-route /visa page for the detail, and verify with the destination's official immigration authority close to your travel date. That order gives you a fast, accurate, and authoritative answer."},{"q":"Does visa-free mean I can stay as long as I want?","a":"No. Visa-free entry almost always comes with a maximum permitted stay for tourism, which varies by destination and can change. Overstaying can lead to fines or future entry problems. Always check the allowed stay length for your specific route, and confirm the current rule with the Visa Wizard before booking your trip."}]''')

FAQS['visa-free-countries-for-vietnam-passport-holders-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"How many countries can Vietnamese passport holders visit visa-free?","a":"Commonly cited visa-free and visa-on-arrival totals for the Vietnamese passport tend to sit somewhere around the 50-ish mark, but this figure shifts as countries change their rules and different sources count differently. Treat any number as a rough guide rather than a hard fact, and confirm each specific destination with the Visa Wizard before you rely on it."},{"q":"Can Vietnamese citizens travel around ASEAN without a visa?","a":"Short tourist trips between ASEAN member states are generally straightforward for Vietnamese passport holders, which is the passport's core strength. That said, allowed stay lengths and exact conditions vary between members and can change, and land entries may differ from air. Confirm the current rule for your specific destination and trip length rather than assuming a single blanket allowance."},{"q":"Is Thailand visa-free for Vietnamese passport holders?","a":"Thailand is an ASEAN neighbour, and short tourist visits are commonly straightforward for Vietnamese travellers, but conditions and stay limits can change. Rather than assume, check the current requirement on the Visa Wizard or the Vietnam to Thailand route page, and confirm against Thai immigration before booking anything non-refundable, especially if your stay is longer than a typical short visit."},{"q":"What is the difference between visa-free and visa on arrival?","a":"Visa-free means you enter with just your passport and receive a stamp, with no application or entry-permit fee. Visa on arrival means you still get a visa, but at the airport or border, usually with a form, a fee and sometimes a photo. Both let you skip applying in advance, but VOA involves a step and a cost that visa-free does not."},{"q":"Can Vietnamese travellers get an e-Visa for India or Sri Lanka?","a":"Destinations such as India and Sri Lanka commonly offer e-Visas that Vietnamese travellers can apply for online before departure, uploading documents and paying a fee for an electronic authorisation. This makes them very accessible even though they are not visa-free. Apply well ahead of your travel dates, and confirm the current process on the official immigration site, as e-Visa systems are updated periodically."},{"q":"Do I still need a passport with months of validity if a country is visa-free?","a":"Yes. Even for visa-free entry, many countries require your passport to be valid for a set period beyond your trip, commonly several months, and may ask for proof of onward travel and funds. Visa-free refers to the entry permit, not these baseline requirements, so check your passport validity and the destination's conditions before you travel."},{"q":"Why does my visa-free list look different from another website's?","a":"Visa rules change frequently, and different sites update at different times and count categories differently, so lists rarely match exactly. Some include visa-on-arrival in their visa-free totals while others do not. This is exactly why a fixed list ages quickly. Use any roundup as a starting point and confirm the live rule for your route with the Visa Wizard and the official authority."},{"q":"Is a visa-on-arrival ever refused at the border?","a":"It can be. Visa on arrival means you are eligible to apply at the border, but approval remains at the immigration officer's discretion, and you may need to show onward tickets, accommodation and sufficient funds. Have your documents ready and meet the conditions. If your trip is important or non-refundable, an e-Visa applied for in advance can give you more certainty than relying on VOA."}]''')

FAQS['visa-free-countries-for-kenya-passport-holders-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"How many countries can Kenyan passport holders enter without a visa in 2026?","a":"Commonly cited totals sit somewhere around 70-ish destinations when you combine visa-free, visa-on-arrival and easy e-Visa access — but the exact number shifts and depends on how each category is counted. Treat any figure as approximate and confirm your specific destination with the Visa Wizard before booking."},{"q":"Can Kenyans travel to Tanzania without a visa?","a":"Movement within the East African Community, which commonly includes Tanzania, tends to be among the easiest travel for Kenyan citizens, often supporting overland trips. Terms still vary by purpose of visit and can change, so check the current Kenya-to-Tanzania requirement on VisitPlane and the official immigration authority before you travel."},{"q":"What's the difference between visa-free and visa on arrival for Kenyans?","a":"Visa-free means you enter with just your passport and no application or fee at the border. Visa on arrival means you don't apply in advance but still get the visa at the airport or land border, often paying a fee. Both are convenient, but only visa-free involves nothing to do on entry."},{"q":"Does the African Union free-movement agenda mean Kenyans can travel anywhere in Africa?","a":"Not yet, and not automatically. The African Union's free-movement agenda aims to make travel across the continent easier for Africans, and it tends to widen access over time. But it rolls out unevenly, country by country, so it's momentum rather than a blanket rule. Always confirm each destination's current entry terms."},{"q":"Can Kenyan passport holders visit Southeast Asia without a visa?","a":"Kenyans commonly have visa-free or visa-on-arrival access to several Southeast Asian destinations popular with tourists, while others use e-Visas. The length of stay and whether entry is free or paid vary by country and can change. Check each destination individually with the Visa Wizard before relying on it for your trip."},{"q":"Why do visa-free lists for Kenya keep changing?","a":"Visa rules move for political and operational reasons: governments sign or suspend agreements, respond to security or health events, switch destinations between VOA and e-Visa, or adjust fees and stay lengths. Reciprocity also plays a role. A static list is accurate only the day it's written, which is why a live check is more reliable."},{"q":"Do I still need documents if a country is visa-free for Kenyans?","a":"Usually yes. Even where no visa is needed, immigration officers commonly ask for a passport valid well beyond your trip, proof of onward travel, and sometimes proof of funds or accommodation. Carrying these smooths entry almost everywhere. Requirements vary by destination, so confirm the specifics before you travel."},{"q":"What's the most reliable way to confirm my visa requirement before booking?","a":"Start with the VisitPlane Visa Wizard for the current requirement, then open the specific per-route visa page for your journey, and finally verify on the destination's official immigration or foreign-ministry website close to booking. The official published rule is the one the border officer applies, so it's the final word."}]''')

FAQS['visa-free-countries-for-ghana-passport-holders-2026'] = json.loads(r'''[{"q":"How many countries can Ghanaians visit visa-free in 2026?","a":"Commonly cited figures put it at around 60-ish destinations across visa-free and visa-on-arrival access, but this number shifts as countries change their policies. Treat any total as a rough indicator of passport strength rather than a fixed fact, and confirm your specific route with the Visa Wizard before booking."},{"q":"Does ECOWAS free movement mean Ghanaians need no documents in West Africa?","a":"No. ECOWAS free movement generally makes travel within member states easier and usually removes the advance-visa step, but you still need a valid passport or approved travel document, you still pass identity checks, and stay limits still apply. Individual countries can adjust requirements, so confirm the current rules for your route before you travel."},{"q":"Can a Ghanaian travel from Ghana to Nigeria without a visa?","a":"Travel between Ghana and Nigeria is generally easier because both are ECOWAS members, which often means no advance visa is required for regional movement. However, you still need valid documents and must clear immigration. Rules can change, so confirm the current Ghana-to-Nigeria requirement on the Visa Wizard and the official immigration authority before departure."},{"q":"Is Kenya visa-free for Ghanaian passport holders?","a":"Kenya is frequently cited as relatively open to Ghanaian travellers, often via visa-free or electronic-authorisation entry, but East African entry policies have changed in recent years. Because the category can shift, do not assume — check the current Ghana-to-Kenya requirement on the Visa Wizard and the official Kenyan immigration authority before you book."},{"q":"What is the difference between visa-on-arrival and an e-Visa for Ghanaians?","a":"Visa-on-arrival means you obtain the visa at the border or airport when you land, usually for a fee. An e-Visa means you apply and pay online before travelling and arrive with an electronic authorisation. Both differ from true visa-free entry. Always confirm which applies to your route, as countries regularly switch between the two."},{"q":"Do Ghanaians need a visa for Rwanda?","a":"Rwanda is often listed among the more accessible African destinations for Ghanaian travellers, frequently offering visa-free or on-arrival entry. That said, policies evolve, so this should not be taken as guaranteed. Verify the current Ghana-to-Rwanda requirement using the Visa Wizard and Rwanda's official immigration authority close to your travel date."},{"q":"Can Ghanaians visit European or Schengen countries visa-free?","a":"As a rule, Schengen and most European countries are not visa-free for Ghanaian passport holders and require an advance visa application. This guide focuses on regions where access is commonly easier, mainly Africa and select islands. For any European trip, confirm the specific requirement and apply through the official channel well ahead of travel."},{"q":"How far in advance should I check my visa requirement?","a":"Check as early as planning allows, then recheck close to departure, because rules can change between booking and travel. Start with the Visa Wizard to identify the category, review the per-route /visa page for details, and confirm with the destination's official immigration authority — especially for e-Visas, which may need processing time."}]''')

ORDER = list(META.keys())

def build_entry(slug):
    m = META[slug]
    faq_lines = ''
    for item in FAQS[slug]:
        faq_lines += "\n      { q: '%s', a: '%s' }," % (ts(item['q']), ts(item['a']))
    return (
"  {\n"
f"    slug: '{slug}',\n"
f"    title: '{ts(m['title'])}',\n"
f"    date: '2026-06-27',\n"
"    excerpt:\n"
f"      '{ts(m['excerpt'])}',\n"
"    category: 'Travel Tips',\n"
f"    readTime: '{m['readTime']}',\n"
f"    coverEmoji: '{m['coverEmoji']}',\n"
f"    passportCountry: '{m['passport']}',\n"
f"    destinationCountry: '{m['dest']}',\n"
"    visaLink: '/wizard',\n"
"    ctaTitle: 'Check your visa with the VisitPlane Wizard',\n"
f"    faqs: [{faq_lines}\n    ],\n"
"  },\n"
    )

def main():
    src = open(SP).read()
    anchor = 'export const blogPosts: BlogPost[] = [\n'
    i = src.find(anchor)
    assert i >= 0, 'anchor not found'
    insert_at = i + len(anchor)
    added = []
    blocks = ''
    for slug in ORDER:
        if ("slug: '%s'" % slug) in src:
            print('SKIP (exists):', slug); continue
        blocks += build_entry(slug)
        added.append(slug)
    src = src[:insert_at] + blocks + src[insert_at:]
    open(SP, 'w').write(src)
    print('Inserted %d entries:' % len(added))
    for s in added: print('  +', s)

main()
